  "title": "Factory Manager #69761",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturing/ Food Production</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Factory Manager</strong></li><li>Working Location: Senoko</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon – Fri, 8 am – 5 pm; Sat, 8 am – 12 pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage the day-to-day operations of the factory, including production processes, warehouse, and logistics operations, ensuring efficiency, quality, and timely delivery of products.</li><li>Develop and implement sales strategies to increase revenue for the company, leveraging industry contacts as appropriate.</li><li>Responsible for coordination and control of production processes to maintain yield.</li><li>Develop and implement safety protocols and standards to ensure a safe working environment for all employees.</li><li>Manage the budget for the factory, including the cost of materials, labour, and overhead expenses.</li><li>Train, supervise and manage the factory staff to ensure that all employees are performing their duties effectively and efficiently.</li><li>Keep up to date with industry trends and developments to ensure that the company remains competitive.</li><li>Address areas of non-compliance as and when appropriate in a professional manner.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in managing Central Kitchen operations.</li><li>Strong background in overseeing large-scale food production.</li><li>Familiar with the Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) Act.</li><li>Familiar with factory automation and manufacturing technology.</li><li>Working knowledge of MS Office is necessary.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#69761 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
